component_name.name: string
component_name.description: Holds the name of the component that is loading

loading_state.description: Object that holds the loading state object coming from dash-renderer

setProps.description:
Dash-assigned callback that should be called whenever any of the
properties change

id.description:
The ID of this component, used to identify dash components
in callbacks. The ID needs to be unique across all of the
components in an app.

style.description: Defines CSS styles which will override styles previously set.

className.description: Often used with CSS to style elements with common properties.

value.description: The value to display in the box. Usually a number or short text.

width.description:
The width of the box, using the Bootstrap grid system. This is
used for row-based layouts. The overall width of a region is 12, so the
default width of 4 occupies 1/3 of that width. Default: 3.

color.description:
A color for the value box, options: primary, secondary, success, info, warning, danger or NULL.
Default: NULL.

href.description: An optional URL to link to.
